Drunks of Tunare, Brell Serilis</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueidolonfaer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eidolon Faer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 266<br> <font color=#CC9900>(2/8/01 8:20:49 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://home.sprynet.com/~kubik01/eqpics/Sigpic.jpg height=233 width=103></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why don't clerics get any illusions?</span><hr size=1> Basically the problem is that Verant is terribly uncreative.  Or at least, all its creative people are on the Star Warez project.<br>
<br>
The Verant Vision(TM) is based on the AD&amp;D Cleric.  Period.  This is unfortunate and limited.  Remember the 2nd level AD&amp;D spell &quot;Spiritual Hammer&quot;?  Well guess what?  Replace 2 with 55 and its the same spell.<br>
<br>
Some things that would fit the role of the Cleric, but which Verant will never implement:<br>
<br>
(1)  A Cleric directs religious rituals for the veneration of his deity.  How about a group-based spell which, if the group has characters of matching religion to the Cleric, serves to replentish the Cleric's Mana Pool.<br>
<br>
(2)  Clerics are used to dealing with spirits and entities of other planes of existence.  Arguably even more so than Magicians.  As long as the Cleric stays on his God's good side, he can, in DIRE emergencies call upon servitors of his deity for aid.<br>
<br>
This would mean that every Cleric would have a separate faction with his god (woe unto Dark Elf Clerics with full suits of Ethereal Mist Armor) and would have a Pet summon series which had minimum levels of this faction to cast and cost faction points everytime they are used.  Probably expensive reagents as well.  The upside would be that this &quot;pet&quot; would be something no mere Mage could hope to control or bind.  Call them &quot;Demi Urges&quot; (29), &quot;Urges&quot; (39), &quot;Dominions&quot; (49), and &quot;Avatars&quot; (60).  And yes, this would mean that 2 full groups of Dark Elf Clerics, after a month of faction work, could each summon an Avatar of Innoruuk and rip through the Plane of Growth.  Piss off your deity though and an attempt to summon one of these guys would probably be spectacularly fatal.<br>
<br>
(3)  Deity Specific spells are a great idea, as are deity-specific items.  A pity that Verant has not done much with these yet.  The Imbue Gemstone spells are in general only slightly less useful than the Enchanter &quot;Mana Vial&quot; series, and only a few of the Cleric Amulet quests have been implemented. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufenye.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fenye</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Queen of Discord</span><br>  Posts: 1441<br> <font color=#CC9900>(2/9/01 9:23:25 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://people.mn.mediaone.net/timelord81/images/fenye.jpg hieght=285 width=129></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why don't clerics get any illusions?</span><hr size=1> I have ALWAYS pondered about this, Yshaa, I really have. I have always thought of clerics as thier diety's most faithful followeres, and as such they should get MORE than just the abilities to heal and buff and do some less-than-adequate dd spells. I thought it would be neat for a cleric to turn into a being of light (or dark) as an illusion, but it wouldn't be just an illusion...<br>
<br>
I always thought it would be hella cool if a cleric could turn into this being of light (might look like a big ass wisp or something, but not buzzing around incessantly like wisps do) and regain hp and mana back faster, or maybe just hp back, or maybe just mana back, or whatever.. <br>
<br>
oh well. I think VI thinks clerics are balanced enough to where they won't mess with them anymore. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uorri.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Orri</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Fire Brand</span><br>  Posts: 274<br> <font color=#CC9900>(2/11/01 3:29:42 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why don't clerics get any illusions?</span><hr size=1> I think clerics should get more deity specific items.<br>
<br>
Followers of evil gods, for example, might get illusion:undead or charm undead.<br>
<br>
Followers of good gods might get some divine intervention spell like summon avatar which would summon a very powerful pet which only lasts for 10 or so tiks, or maybe they could get more beneficial heals at earlier levels.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utryyall.showPublicProfile?language=EN>tryyall</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#CC9900>(2/12/01 3:47:45 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why don't clerics get any illusions?</span><hr size=1> <br>
