 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uahzag.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ahzag</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#CC9900>(2/12/01 8:01:24 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why don't clerics get any illusions?</span><hr size=1> I think the last thing that we should be asking for is further muddling of the classes.  One of the reasons most people became dissapointed with UO is that basically above a certain level the charachters fit into 2 templates.  EQ was a breath of fresh air with distinct charachter types that had very different contributions to groups.  As they have attempted to balance the classes what they have actually done is give them each others abilities.  This muddling of the classes has, in my opinion, actually made the strong classes even stronger.  Who really needs a shaman when the enchanter can slow the mob and give you an even larger dex bump than the shaman can? So I dont think it would be wise to start giving clerics enchantments.<br>
<br>
Ahzag Azule <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umarzen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>marzen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#CC9900>(2/15/01 9:16:36 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why don't clerics get any illusions?</span><hr size=1> Although I would not want an illusion spell. The answer I always see is others don't think clerics really need anything else. Although when I signed up to be a cleric I like the ideal of being a prim healer, but can attack if I need to, such as a stun or a root or fear or dd(rarely). The problem as I see it is once they started mudding up the class to create this world of balance for the most part our class got left out. The few spells we got at higher levels such as celestrial healing, group symbol and 96% rez are the only real good spells. Although now with rez on a stick at 51 that sucks, but one day I might work on it again. The deity spell ideal is a great one and I would like a real pet not for attacking but a defender, even if i could only cast the spell once a day. The ideal that they can balance the other class without giving the cleric anything new is a sad day. Clerics we need to truely think hard as a group and come up with a few good improvements that maybe others will take us seriously on pushing for the change. To those that like this class the writing on the wall to get rid of this class, so keep your eyes open once they give complete heal no more clerics(only spell left to go). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubenferoz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BenFeroz</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_2.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#CC9900>(2/15/01 4:19:23 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why don't clerics get any illusions?</span><hr size=1> My 2 cents...If a cleric had an illusion of undead they would be a necro, if a cleric had a decent pet, they would play around with that and not pay attention to healing and tanks would die. The only thing, in my opinion, that clerics need is a better way to regen mana. C'mon, at 200 wisdom, and mana gear...it takes an insanely long time to get to FM, we're talking 5 to 10 minutes unless we are upped on caster crack. That results in way too much downtime. Another thing that may be nice however is a group gate spell, evacing the group to the clerics bind point not half-way accross Norrath. <br>
<br>
Benwalin Ferroz<br>
49th Cleric of Tunare<br>
<br>
&quot;Your eyes only see what they want to see, your heart makes true what you want to believe&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bbrellserilis.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=geneive>geneive</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 81<br> <font color=#CC9900>(2/25/01 1:53:34 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why don't clerics get any illusions?</span><hr size=1> LOL Tryyall good advice, but despite your saying &quot;Being ANON works wonders, people can never find you unless you are already on their Friends list,&quot; you're one of the clerics I know who is rarely anon.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I don't think we should get illusions or more pets, but I do agree with Tryllium and several other clerics who suggest that we get a self-only invisibility -- makes those CR/res runs a lot safer.  The first question I always ask nowadays upon res request is where's the body, so I can determine how much I have to risk dying to get to someone else's res -- but fortunately everyone I've helped recently has had their corpse dragged to zoneline.<br>
<br>
Hmmm on second thought, invis/invis-to-undead aren't compatible...wish we could have a illusion of zombie or spectre that would be fun and give undead invis, and then on top of it we could cast our self-invis, and get safely through hell holes like Lower Guk.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :eek --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eek.gif ALT=":eek"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Or a invis Illusion of the Gods and then cast our undead invis on top of it.  Heehee maybe Illusion of the Gods could be deity-specific and turn you into a female High Elf (Tunare), male Dark Elf (Innoruuk), etc...which would be hilarious if your character were the opposite sex to begin with.<br>
